Subject: drm/amdgpu: asd function needs to be unloaded in suspend phase
Git-commit: 20303ec5d2165ee6344190274bc59118921f71d9
Patch-mainline: v5.8-rc5
References: jsc#SLE-12680, jsc#SLE-12880, jsc#SLE-12882, jsc#SLE-12883, jsc#SLE-13496, jsc#SLE-15322

Unload ASD function in suspend phase.

Signed-off-by: Huang Rui <ray.huang@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c
index 7301fdcfb8bc..83bceb65ff80 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c
@@ -1840,6 +1840,12 @@ static int psp_suspend(void *handle)
 		}
 	}
 
+	ret = psp_asd_unload(psp);
+	if (ret) {
+		DRM_ERROR("Failed to unload asd\n");
+		return ret;
+	}
+
 	ret = psp_ring_stop(psp, PSP_RING_TYPE__KM);
 	if (ret) {
 		DRM_ERROR("PSP ring stop failed\n");
